						<div class="postbody">snarfblASM makes a distinction between 8- and 16-bit values, similar to the way that C would distinguish between "short int" and "char" values.
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">zpAddress1 = $02<br />absoluteAddress1 = $0002<br /><br />.enum 0<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; zpAddress2: .dsb<br />.ende<br /><br />.org $8000<br />absoluteAddress2:<br /></div></div>

